Inline tables provide a compact syntax for expressing tables on a single line. They are enclosed in curly braces with comma-separated key/value pairs. Inline tables are intended to be self-contained and cannot be extended later.

```toml
[dependencies]
serde = "1.0"
serde_json = "1.0"
tokio = { version = "1", features = ["full"] }
my-lib = { path = "../my-lib" }
fork = { git = "https://github.com/user/fork", branch = "main" }
optional-dep = { version = "0.5", optional = true }
```
**Cargo.toml** — The `[dependencies]` section lists crate dependencies. Values can be simple version strings or tables with version, features, path, git, branch, optional, and default-features.
